Overview

Groupe Dynamite Inc. (GDI) is a Montréal-based, privately held house of integrated omni-channel brands, designing and distributing accessible, trend-forward fashion for women since 1975.

Our mission of "Empowering YOU to be YOU, one outfit at a time" is brought to life through the GARAGE and DYNAMITE banners and represents the consumer-centric core of GDI's long-standing success as a leading retailer in North America.

Today, GDI operates nearly 300 stores across Canada and the United States, as well as shoppable brand experiences at Garageclothing.com and Dynamiteclothing.com.

Overview:

Reporting into the Divisional Merchandise Director, you will provide leadership and product line management for all facets of the merchandising process. You will work in cross-functional teams to successfully develop, design, and manage merchandise to drive a product line that meets business plans and long term vision.

Main Responsibilities:
• Drive current/future growth of the department through the development of merchandise assortments;
• Develop a track record of success by consistently delivering on or above target results to plan;
• Develop creative and innovative strategies to drive a business plan;
• Understand and analyze competition and marketplace to enhance customer focus and develop innovative ideas;
• Manage OTB in order to drive and build business strategies;
• Work in conjunction with planning to manage the OTB as far as receipts, sales, margin, markdowns and weeks of stock;
• Lead and manage the line planning, pricing, and product creation process including style/color plan, and sizing strategy;
• Analyze performance and plans to help identify sales and margin opportunities that can exceed plan;
• Constant pursuit of providing trend right product to the customer and driving department growth through assortment planning;
• Quickly adapt to changes/trends occurring in the business and marketplace;
• Effectively and efficiently lead business meetings; communicate, influence and negotiate with cross-functional teams to execute vision;
• Collaborate with the visual team and ongoing management in the development and execution of floor sets;

To qualify for this role, you must have...
• Bachelor’s degree;
• Minimum 3 years experience in fashion buying and/or fashion product management;
• Excellent sense of style and knowledge of fashion trends;
• Strong product knowledge and a balance of analytical and creative abilities to positively affect the bottom line;
• Strong financial acumen and analytical skills;
• Language of work: French or English, excellent communication skills in English (written and spoken) are required in order to deal with international suppliers;
• Solid planning skills with experience managing an Open-to-Buy;
• Strong ability to work in teams and leadership skills;
• Good computer skills (Excel and/or equivalent software systems);
• In-depth understanding of our brand and its target market.

To be a great fit, you must...
• Be able to make tough decisions;
• Thrive in the face of change with a strong sense of urgency;
• Challenge the status quo by contributing impactful ideas and solutions;
• Build partnerships and prioritize collaboration;
• Present information in an effective and concise manner;
• Be proactive and exceed expected results.

At GDI, You Will Be Part Of a Growing Organization That Understands The Importance Of Investing In People And Offers You:
• A comprehensive compensation package that includes performance-driven bonuses;
• A group retirement savings program with employer matching;
• Flexible group insurance with personalized coverage that meets your needs;
• An employee discount at Garage and Dynamite; Exclusive private sample sales;
• A flexible vacation policy;
• And more!

GDI has been repeatedly voted one of Montréal’s Top Employers and one of Canada’s Top Employers for Young People.

Our promise…

No day will be like the last—we aim to be better today than we were yesterday. We are committed to employment equity.

Candidates that are retained will be called for an interview.

Une équipe aux mille et un talents unie dans sa diversité

Nous sommes une entreprise d’ici qui imagine de la lingerie et des maillots de bain faits pour la vraie vie depuis très longtemps. Et pourquoi? Parce qu’on veut que les femmes du monde entier se sentent bien dans leur peau. Joins-toi à notre équipe dynamique afin de débuter une carrière professionnelle stimulante dans un environnement engagé et en constante évolution.

Nous sommes plus de 4,600 employés et nous avons plus de 287 boutiques à l'échelle du Canada et notre marque est aussi présente dans 19 pays (100 magasins) un peu partout dans le monde.

Des Extras Juste Pour Les Membres De Notre Équipe
• Rabais de 50 % sur nos produits;
• Horaires flexibles;
• Possibilités d'avancement au sein de l'entreprise;
• Entreprise familiale engagée dans la communauté;
• Bonis de rendement (postes de gestion ou de ventes en magasin);
• Programme de reconnaissance pour les années de service;
• Programme d'innovation visant à encourager le partage d'idées;
• Boni de référence;
• Dayforce Wallet (paie sur demande : tu auras la possibilité d’avoir accès à une partie de ta paie dès la fin de ton quart de travail).

Pour Les Employé.e.s à Temps Plein
• Régime d’assurance collective;
• De trois (3) à cinq (5) jours de congé personnel (selon le poste);
• Cotisation de l’employeur minimum de 2% versée à ton REER.

BANNIERE : LA VIE EN ROSE

rue Wellington

Tu Es La Personne Qu'il Nous Faut Si
• Tu as déjà de l’expérience en tant qu’assistant.e gérant.e dans le domaine du commerce au détail;
• Tu aimes les vêtements qui célèbrent la féminité sous toutes ses formes;
• Tu es un.e leader dans l’âme et tu sais comment motiver une équipe;
• Tu as de l’entregent et tout un esprit d’équipe;
• Tu aimes avoir des objectifs et tu les atteins toujours;
• Tu es proactif.ve et tu fais preuve de tact;
• Tu cherches un emploi qui t’offre toujours de nouveaux défis à relever;
• Tu es prêt.e à travailler pendant les jours fériés et au-delà du plafond d’heures prévues pendant les périodes achalandées (selon tes disponibilités).

Tu as envie de mettre ton talent de gestionnaire à contribution? Nous t’invitons à partager notre quotidien rempli de plaisir et de défis professionnels !

Ce à Quoi Pourraient Ressembler Tes Journées

Sous la supervision du ou de la gérant.e, tu devras veiller au bon fonctionnement de la boutique et t’assurer que ton équipe offre un service à la clientèle remarquable. Lorsque tu remplaceras le ou la gérant.e, tu seras responsable d’atteindre les objectifs généraux, de maintenir nos standards d’entreprise et de motiver ton équipe à se surpasser.

Ventes
• Optimiser le rendement et la profitabilité de ta boutique avec l’aide de ton équipe de gestion;
• Former les membres de ton équipe pour les aider à bien accompagner la clientèle : leur enseigner les meilleures techniques de vente et t’assurer qu’ils maitrisent bien toutes les caractéristiques des produits;
• Analyser les résultats de ventes avec le ou la gérant.e et trouver des solutions innovantes pour les faire croitre;
• Gérer la masse salariale de façon rentable grâce à une bonne planification des horaires en fonction du rendement des employé.e.s;
• Communiquer des objectifs de ventes à ton équipe pour t’assurer de les atteindre ou de les surpasser;
• Accueillir chaleureusement la clientèle et répondre à ses questions afin de l’aider à trouver les morceaux parfaits.
• Comment? En parlant des caractéristiques techniques, de la qualité et des matériaux des produits;
• Coordonner les actions avec l’équipe de gestion et garantir la continuité et la bonne marche des activités en son absence.

Ressources humaines
• Mobiliser ton équipe pour créer un environnement de travail positif qui favorise la recherche de l’excellence, en plus de développer le sentiment d’appartenance et la fierté de travailler pour la Vie en Rose;
• Faire vivre notre vision, notre mission ainsi que notre culture sur le terrain et la transmettre à ton équipe;
• Faire preuve de leadership et être un modèle inspirant en tout temps;
• Apprendre à bâtir une équipe performante, ce qui veut dire recruter, préparer et former la relève et identifier les meilleur.e.s candidat.e.s potentiel.le.s pour les divers postes;
• Planifier les horaires de travail et les communiquer aux membres de l’équipe, en plus de gérer leurs absences et leurs retards;
• Participer aux évaluations de rendement de toute l’équipe de la boutique;
• Assurer une bonne planification des horaires en fonction du rendement des membres de ton équipe et de l’achalandage.

Marketing et présentation visuelle
• Connaitre la marchandise et les particularités techniques des produits sur le bout de tes doigts;
• Créer une boutique attrayante et invitante selon nos planogrammes avec l’aide de ton équipe;
• Être à l’affût de ce que fait la concurrence et de l’activité du marché;
• Bâtir une clientèle régulière et fidèle en communiquant l’image de marque et en établissant des liens dans le domaine du commerce au détail;
• Aider à la planification de la réception de marchandises et assurer la mise en place rapide de la présentation visuelle;
• Participer à la gestion de l’allure et de la propreté de la boutique et de l’arrière-boutique;
• Collaborer avec l’administration du centre commercial.

Administration
• Analyser les différents rapports pour optimiser la productivité et les ventes;
• Procéder à l’ouverture et à la fermeture de ta boutique;
• Gérer toutes les dépenses contrôlables de ta boutique de façon efficace;
• Respecter et appliquer les politiques et procédures des différents services du siège social (on va tout t’expliquer);
• Accomplir d’autres tâches connexes pour aider l’équipe, au besoin.

PERMANENT, TEMPS PLEIN

Les informations sur ce site sont uniquement à des fins d'information et ne sont pas destinées à avoir des conséquences juridiques. La Vie en Rose s'est engagée envers l'équité en matière d'emploi. La Vie en Rose a mis en place un processus d'adaptation prévoyant des mesures d'adaptation pour les candidats sélectionnés pour une entrevue.

Outside Sales Representative

Status

Regular, Full time

Location:

Montréal, Quebec

Job Description

Do you like sales? Are you looking for a new professional challenge?

We are currently looking for an Outside Sales Representative who will develop profitable sales and ensure that customer expectations are consistently met, thereby maximizing our market share. Join our team now!

Why would you like working at Guillevin?
• Earn more: you'll be offered a competitive salary and a share in our generous profit-sharing program, which recognizes the individual contributions of our employees.
• Career development: we encourage employees to build an interesting and stimulating career with opportunities for advancement and continuing education. We give employees the chance to develop their autonomy, professional skills and competencies.
• Benefits: Our benefits package includes a group health insurance program (paramedical, dental, drug, vision and vision care, employee assistance program and telemedicine); a generous RRSP contribution; the possibility of contributing to a TFSA with an advantageous group rate; a Postsecondary Scholarship Program for our employees' children, and much more! Discover the benefits you'll enjoy once you've chosen a job at Guillevin.

The day-to-day tasks of an Outside Sales Representative
• Develop account strategies that meet the business center's sales objectives;
• Develop profitable incremental sales for new and existing accounts;
• Coordinate sales and customer service efforts with inside sales and purchasing;
• Support inside sales and quoting specialists to drive excellent customer service, operational efficiency and account profitability;
• Ensure in-depth and up-to-date knowledge of customers, as well as competitors' strengths and weaknesses;
• Develop and maintain long-term relationships with customers and supplier representatives;
• Develop solutions to customer problems;
• Provide accurate market information to the Business Center Manager and other members of the sales team;
• Maintain up-to-date technical knowledge of various product lines.

Outside Sales Representative profile
• Minimum of five (5) years industry experience preferred and at least two (2) years sales experience or a combination of relevant professional training and experience;
• Demonstrated sales ability;
• Excellent communication and organizational skills;
• Excellent oral and written French;
• Product knowledge;
• Must be customer service and results oriented;
• Computer experience an asset.

What’s In It For You

We are a major player, involved in the energy transformation in Canada. Certified as a Great Place to Work®, we offer a dynamic work environment with great career opportunities. We promote autonomy and decision making.

What Sets Us Apart Is Our
• Annual profit-sharing offered to all in addition to our competitive compensation: rewarding accomplishments is part of our culture.
• A strong national network offering real opportunities to grow: our people make the difference.

Among Our Benefits
• Flexible group insurance plan customizable to your needs.
• Free health resources available 24/7: Telemedicine and Employee Assistance Program (EAP).
• Group RRSP with employer contribution and TFSA.
• Postsecondary Scholarship Program for our employee’s children.
• Charging terminals available at our facilities.
• Years of Service Recognition Program.

Come build your career with us, a growing network where our people make it happen!

Our recruitment process ensures equality and diversity. Please note that only successful candidates will be contacted.

Company Profile

Located in Montreal, PSB BOISJOLI is one of Quebec’s leading accounting firms, with a team of over 250 people. The Firm values an approach based on mutual support and teamwork amongst Partners and ledger team members PSB. It also offers a competitive salary and benefits as well as a stimulating working environment that fosters professional growth.

PSB BOISJOLI is currently seeking an Accounting Supervisor to join its team.

Responsibilities
• Responsible for completing and finalizing mandates (i.e. subsequent adjustments to file, clearing of partner/manager review notes, and ensures that all necessary documentation and correspondence is received and filed appropriately);
• Resolve semi-complex technical issues and escalate unresolved complex issues to the appropriate higher-level person;
• Identifies and brings any changes in circumstances to the attention of the Manager;
• GST/QST: understands basic concepts and compliance, and identifies and resolves issues;
• Prepares complete working paper files relating to Compilation and Review engagements, and ensures that all work is documented appropriately;
• Personal Taxes: Able to review complex tax returns, identifies potential problems and tax planning opportunities, and communicates these to the Manager;
• Corporate Taxes: Able to identify potential problems, and has a general understanding of, among other things, partnership and relationship rules, active vs. passive tax rules, CDA account and donation rules;
• Ensures that issues raised by clients and/or the existence of potential clients are communicated to engagement partners and senior managers;
• Reviews taxable benefits and DAS calculations.

Qualifications and experience
• Minimum of 5 years work experience in an accounting firm
• CPA designation
• Excellent written and verbal skills;
• Bilingual (French and English);
• Strong planning and organizational skills
• Strong time management skills
• Knowledge of investment brokerage bookkeeping
• Proficient in Microsoft Office as well as CaseWare/CaseView and TaxPrep.

We thank all candidates for their application and interest in our Firm. However, we will only be contacting those applicants that we are interested in pursuing.

Analyst Consultant - US ABL Lender Consulting Group

Richter Montreal Office

Richter Consulting, Inc. (“RCI”) is a member of the Richter Group. RCI serves its clients with a multidisciplinary group of 6 partners and ~20 professionals. We work with US-based leverage lenders, private equity firms, and major banks regarding their portfolio companies/investments. Our clients call upon our experienced professionals to provide our expertise in Asset-Based Lending Diligence, as well as Business Assessment, Cash Flow Forecasting, Financial Reorganization/Profitability Improvement, Crisis Management, and Transaction Advisory, among other services.

A Career With a High Rate Of Return

What’s in it for you?
• Experience in a specialized, highly-regarded consulting practice;
• Exposure to sophisticated companies within a variety of industries;
• Contribute to a customized work product with tangible results and actionable recommendations;
• Become a more well-rounded professional, developing soft and technical skills;
• Work directly with experienced Partners;
• Join a dynamic team committed to investing in your development;
• Opportunity to travel periodically to large cities across the United States;
• Competitive performance bonus;
• Competitive group benefits which include group insurance, health spending account, savings plans, and employer contribution matching;

Position Overview

Richter Consulting is looking to hire an experienced professional at the analyst level in their Asset Based Lending diligence practice. While this position is based in Montreal and Toronto, our engagements are primarily carried out in major US cities. Our engagements involve a risk-based approach to collateral reviews for leading US financial institutions and are often utilized for refinancing and turnaround. Our deal teams of 3-4 professionals deliver asset-based lending consultation services involving companies in numerous industries (Consumer Products, Retail, Manufacturing, Distribution, Services, etc.).

Must Haves
• 2-5 years of relevant experience (CPA)
• Excellent communication (written and verbal), presentation, and organizational skills;
• Ability to rapidly identify key issues during an engagement and make recommendations;
• Superior financial analysis skills and proficiency with Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint;
• Proficiency with data analysis tools (Power BI, Microsoft Access, and IDEA) an asset;
• Strong teamwork and interpersonal skills;
• Flexibility to work from home or hybrid work environment;
• Some US travel required (~15%)

What We Are Looking For
• Strong aptitude for quantitative and qualitative analyses and ability to link findings to strategy;
• Review and analysis of financial data and trends relating to the collateral and the borrower’s business;
• Assessments of collateral borrowing base;
• Evaluation of financial reporting systems;
• Regular communications with lenders through written reports and exit interviews;
• Ability to work autonomously in a fast-paced environment among driven professionals;
• Occasional involvement in other engagements such as business assessments, liquidity reviews, operational/profitability improvements, corporate finance, and due diligence.

Our client, a national law firm, is currently seeking for lawyers with between 2 to 5 years of relevant experience in a transactional practice of corporate law and who are interested in joining our Banking and Finance team of twenty seasoned professionals who provide strategic business advice on complex financing transactions to Canadian and international clients in the financial services sector.
In this role, you will be required to work proactively on a wide variety of Canadian and international financial transactions, including large and complex transactions. You will work closely with a diverse and sophisticated client base that includes Canadian companies, multinationals and private equity firms as well as major financial institutions and banks.

Experience requirements:
• 2 to 5 years of corporate transactional experience gained at a large law firm.

Education and Qualifications:
• Bachelor’s degree in law;
• Excellent academic record;
• Member in good standing of the Quebec Bar.

Required skills:
• Excellent legal mind;
• Great communication skills;
• Analytical and synthesis skills;
• Ability to work in a team;
• Commitment to excellence;
• Superior interpersonal skills.

Slater Vecchio has established a growing class action practice and is actively expanding its foot print in Quebec and BC, now and in the long term. We have filed a wide range of class actions, including claims concerning cartels, government actors, systemic abuse, product liability, privacy, and others. See a full list of our class action practices here. We have offices in Vancouver and Montreal and are looking to hire a lawyer to work with and contribute to our class action practice in our Montreal office. This is an exciting opportunity to work across both civil law and common law jurisdictions while embracing the culture and values of a small firm.

As the successful candidate, you will have 1-5 years of general litigation experience, ideally with some past exposure to class action work. You will be fluently and proficiently bilingual (French/English), be a member of the Quebec Bar, and have your common law degree although current membership in any common law province is not necessary.

Duties & responsibilities
• Researching legal issues related to new and ongoing cases;
• Working with clients;
• Writing research memos, drafting pleadings and other legal documents;
• Managing class action litigation files and liaising with main stakeholders involved, such as defense counsel, court and clients;
• Representing clients in court, mediations and in out-of-court negotiations.

We value individuals who demonstrate excellent research and analytical skills. We are looking for those with a strong desire for a professional environment that allows them to reach their full potential, a passion to help others and a medium to promote access to justice.

Slater Vecchio is a team of legal professionals who are driven by principles which put our client’s needs first. This is an opportunity to join one of the leading class action practices in Canada, working with a firm and lawyers that have been consistently ranked as a top legal firm by Canadian Lawyers, Best Lawyers, and The National Trial Lawyers.

Our firm culture encourages growth and development for all our firm members.

We are a hard-working, collegial group of people that support one another and truly enjoy our work. We offer a competitive salary and benefits, including membership fees.

Do you want to be challenged and work in a dynamic and stimulating environment? NanoXplore is the company for you!

You will have the opportunity to work for a fast-growing company that creates sustainable products that push the conventional boundaries in multiple industries. Innovation is part of our core values; and we encourage new ideas whether they are big or small.

Job Purpose

This role will provide critical support to the engineering team, particularly in finalizing the technical designs and overseeing the implementation of manufacturing processes for the anode and graphene project.

Responsabilities
• Design Finalization: Collaborate closely with the engineering team to refine and finalize detailed designs for the anode materials and graphene production process. This includes validating equipment layouts, material flows, and process specifications to ensure optimal performance.
• Process Optimization: Work on optimizing manufacturing processes to improve production efficiency and reduce costs. This will involve identifying opportunities for automation, enhancing material usage, and minimizing waste.
• Technical Oversight: Provide hands-on oversight during the execution phase, ensuring that all equipment and processes are installed and calibrated correctly. Ensure that the manufacturing setup is aligned with both the technical requirements and regulatory standards for battery materials and graphene production.
• Cross-Functional Collaboration: Act as the liaison between the engineering, R&D, and operations teams to ensure that all departments are aligned on project goals and timelines. Provide technical support to other teams where needed.
• Compliance and Safety: Ensure that all designs and processes comply with industry standards, particularly in relation to environmental, health, and safety regulations. This will include regular inspections and audits to maintain a safe working environment.
• Vendor and Supplier Coordination: Work with equipment suppliers and contractors to ensure timely delivery and installation of machinery and other components. Participate in contract negotiations and vendor assessments to ensure that all external partners meet project technical specifications.
• Commissioning and Testing: Oversee the commissioning of production equipment and systems, conducting thorough testing to ensure that performance metrics are achieved. Resolve any technical issues that arise during testing or early-stage production.

Training, degrees:
• Bachelor's degree in chemical or mechanical engineering or any other related field

Experience, knowledge:
• 2 years of North American experience working on mining projects, pharmaceutical, battery or chemical projects;
• Proven experience with Lean Manufacturing principles and Six Sigma methodologies.

Skills, aptitudes:
• Bilingualism (French-English) is required as the successful candidate will be interacting on a regular basis with contacts outside Quebec;
• Strong attention to detail and commitment to quality.
• Ability to manage multiple projects and meet tight deadlines;
• A proactive approach to identifying and solving problems.

Attitude:
• Reliable;
• Hard working;
• Adaptable in the face of shifting priorities;
• Positive attitude;
• Excellent interpersonal skills;
• Ability to work in a team environment.

What we offer:
• RRSP/DPSP program
• Group insurance program including medical and dental coverage;
• Telemedicine program;
• Employee and family assistance program;
• Employee referal program;
• Free on-site gym;
• Regularly organized social events (potluck, BBQ and more);
• Free coffee.

NanoXplore is a graphene company, a manufacturer and supplier of high-volume graphene powder for use in industrial markets. The Corporation provides standard and custom graphene-enhanced plastic and composite products to various customers in transportation, packaging, electronics, and other industrial sectors. NanoXplore is headquartered in Montreal, Quebec, with nearly 400 employees supporting manufacturing facilities across Canada, the U.S. and Switzerland. NanoXplore is a publicly traded Company (TSX; GRA and OTCQX: NNXPF) headquartered in Ville St-Laurent.

